description: Notification of a generated syslog message. Apart from
the jnxSyslogTrap objects, this notification can include
one or more attribute-value pairs. The attribute-value
pairs shall be identified by objects jnxSyslogAvAttribute
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogTrap JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogEventName s EXAMPLE JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogTimestamp s EXAMPLEE JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogSeverity i 1 JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogFacility i 1 JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogProcessId u 9999 JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogProcessName s EXAMPLE JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogHostName s EXAMPLE JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogMessage s EXAMPLE

description: An octet string containing syslog event name.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogEventName

description: Date and Time of syslog message generation.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogTimestamp

description: Identifies the severity of this syslog message.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogSeverity

description: Identified the facility of this syslog message.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogFacility

description: Process-Id of the process that generated this syslog message.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogProcessId

description: Name of the process that generated this syslog message.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogProcessName

description: Hostname of host on which this syslog message is generated.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxSyslogHostName

description: The SNMP trap that will be used only for sending spoofed
traps from customer scripts running from JUNOS.
Value will be a OID to be set and send to NMS using spoof traps.
variables.name: JUNIPER-SYSLOG-MIB::jnxUserDefinedTrapOID
